This paper is likely to belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category as it proposes a method of deep artificial neuromodulation that applies the concepts of biological neuromodulation to stochastic gradient descent. Additionally, the paper discusses evolved neuromodulatory dynamics that modify learning parameters at each layer in a deep neural network over the course of the network's training, which is a common topic in the field of neural and evolutionary computing.

The paper also touches on topics related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, which are covered in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories, respectively.

Furthermore, the paper discusses the application of neuromodulation in computer vision, which falls under the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category.

Finally, the paper discusses the use of neuromodulation in controlling the behavior of a system, which is a topic covered in the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
